ion hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/Blues" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Blues&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/515/082/801/692/129/original/82e67e97247a65b7.jpeg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/515/082/801/692/129/original/82e67e97247a65b7.jpeg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110517169265981427</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 00:49:33 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>The Way of Accountability</title><link>https://mastodon.au/@liberate/110515683831895382</link><description>"Curtis Mayfield" art by @nettiebeatrice 🎨  &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackart" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackartist" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackartist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/afrofuturism" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;afrofuturism&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackjoy" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackjoy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackhistory" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackhistory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackfuturity" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackfuturity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackmastodon" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackmastodon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackfedi" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackfedi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackfediverse" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackfediverse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.au/tags/blackfriday" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;blackfriday&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/515/684/486/239/763/original/4f972e22c76378d1.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/110/515/684/486/239/763/original/4f972e22c76378d1.jpg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110517172673738312</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 00:50:25 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Matteo Carandini</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@MatteoCarandini/110518871584979095</link><description>Delighted to see this paper by Pip Coen, Tim Sit &amp;amp; co "Mouse frontal cortex mediates additive multisensory decisions" out in Neuron: &lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.neuron.2023.05.008" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1016/j.neuron.2023.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;05.008&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;It shows that mice (and in my opinion other species too) integrate auditory and visual signals additively and that prefrontal cortex (area MOs in mouse) is necessary and sufficient for that integration. (Pip has a nice thread on it here: &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/Pipcoen/status/1386948586706030592" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;twitter.com/Pipcoen/status/138&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;6948586706030592&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/518/864/627/964/389/original/3a6832cfd1aa8c18.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/110/518/864/627/964/389/original/3a6832cfd1aa8c18.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110518871584979095</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 08:02:28 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Caroline Orr Bueno</title><link>https://newsie.social/@rvawonk/110515595931909451</link><description>Russian propaganda outlets have been heavily promoting RFK Jr. since he announced his presidential candidacy. This raises major red flags regarding Russian interference in US elections, with RT even promoting Bitcoin donations to RFK’s campaign. My latest: &lt;a href="https://open.substack.com/pub/weaponizedspaces/p/russian-propaganda-outlets-promote?r=1aupz&amp;amp;utm_medium=ios&amp;amp;utm_campaign=post" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;open.substack.com/pub/weaponiz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;edspaces/p/russian-propaganda-outlets-promote?r=1aupz&amp;amp;utm_medium=ios&amp;amp;utm_campaign=post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110519514142796463</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 10:45:53 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Guy Bouvier</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@guy_bouvier/110521115917057176</link><description>Cool preprint alert 🔥🔥! Impaired cerebellar plasticity hypersensitizes sensory reflexes in SCN2A-associated ASD. Super proud of this work that we have done with the Bender lab. Please, let us know if you have any questions/feedback. &lt;a href="https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2023.06.05.543814v1" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;23.06.05.543814v1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110521115917057176</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 17:33:14 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Tim Bray</title><link>https://cosocial.ca/@timbray/110520931689649381</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://saturation.social/@jkottke" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;jkottke&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Jeepers, all this complicated stuff. Drizzle with good olive oil, put ’em on the barbecue next to the chops or burgers or whatever. The key technique is taking them off when they’re showing black bits &amp;amp; will thus be a bit crispy, but before they char.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110521590407574240</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 19:33:54 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Wikipedia</title><link>https://wikis.world/@wikipedia/110521096618539598</link><description>Congrats to our friends at &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://framapiaf.org/@debian" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;debian&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; :debian: on the successful release of the newest version of the "universal operating system": Debian 12, aka Bookworm&lt;a href="https://www.debian.org/News/2023/20230610" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;debian.org/News/2023/20230610&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://wikis.world/tags/Wikipedia" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; runs on &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://wikis.world/tags/Debian" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Debian&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; because of its commitment to stability, security and software freedom. We'll be upgrading to bookworm soon!</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110521596230632806</guid><pubDate>Sat, 10 Jun 2023 19:35:23 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Teri Kanefield</title><link>https://law-and-politics.online/@Teri_Kanefield/110522341524630347</link><description>Hi, everyone,Because of family obligations this weekend, I'll have to do this blog post in two parts.Part I, which is ready, is a close reading and analysis of the indictment itself.Part II: I will talk about what we can expect next, and I'll answer questions. I should have that ready before Tuesday.Here is Part I: &lt;a href="https://terikanefield.com/indictment-2" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;terikanefield.com/indictment-2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110524922314941997</guid><pubDate>Sun, 11 Jun 2023 09:41:15 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>mekka okereke :verified:</title><link>https://hachyderm.io/@mekkaokereke/110522931587008318</link><description>You know the rules: ignore every article on the gender pay gap that doesn't mention race. All of them. At best they are poorly researched. At worst, they are intentionally misleading.This article passes the test... barely... because it mentions that the gap for POC is even wider.&lt;a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/06/08/women-gender-pay-parity" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;axios.com/2023/06/08/women-gen&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;der-pay-parity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;2056 sounds far away, but the pay gap for Black women won't reach parity until the year 2300 AD. For Hispanic women, it's beyond 2400 AD. 🤡&lt;a href="https://hachyderm.io/@mekkaokereke/109906587205614822" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;hachyderm.io/@mekkaokereke/109&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;906587205614822&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110525021432483238</guid><pubDate>Sun, 11 Jun 2023 10:06:28 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>David Schoppik</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@schoppik/110525035701945869</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mathstodon.xyz/@neuralengine"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;neuralengine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@NicoleCRust"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;NicoleCRust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://fediscience.org/@DrYohanJohn"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;DrYohanJohn&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; 👋</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110525035701945869</guid><pubDate>Sun, 11 Jun 2023 10:10:05 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Joe Cardillo (they/them)</title><link>https://federate.social/@joecardillo/110523011684624829</link><description>If you’re a job seeker (or know someone), here is a thread with 30+ remote jobs, incl. transparent salary/pay 🧵The Sunrise Project is hiring a Senior Communications Campaigner ($88-111K): &lt;a href="https://www.mattlockshin.com/job-board" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;mattlockshin.com/job-board&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Neighborhood Funders Group is hiring a Program Officer ($90-100K) and Senior Director ($160K) for the Amplify Fund: &lt;a href="https://www.blackremoteshe.com/job-board" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;blackremoteshe.com/job-board&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/s